content: Build success! SVN 14158, 0e1d020de43e5c6c172c49d996c57d28ee04acad

You'll see these messages now from MS Visual Studio Team Services -- I'm running this and travis at the same time so we can compare head to head. Right now VSTS should be faster, but we'll see how stable. And the output logs from the VSTS build aren't publicly visible (yet -- I should be able to turn this feature on next week; meanwhile @Grahame Grieve if you want access to the web-based console let me know).
great, thanks. Hopefully the zulip message can include a string error message if the build produces one...

Sure; so far I've just been working on feature parity with Travis (our Travis notifications haven't included detailed fialure inline, right?)

Customizing the notifications with this new setup should be very straightforward, though (basically, we have a bash script that runs on success, and another on failure.

right. travis just produces pass/fail. and then you have to mine the logs, which is not always easy and not all committers do correctly. I think I'll have to produce a particular output for the build to use as the one liner...

Yeah, if you can give me a good one-liner and tell me how find it (e.g. check a specific file, or grep a specific file for the line starting with "Build failure summary:", or whatever... that'll be straightforward.
ok. I'll let you know
